### System:
You are an AI assistant that follows instruction extremely well. Help as much as you can.

### User:
what does this command do: ssh -i "~/UserKey.pem" -C -L 25900:localhost:5900 user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com

### Response:


The command is used to connect to a remote server using SSH (Secure Shell). 

The `ssh` command is followed by the hostname of the remote server, followed by a colon and then the port number that the user wants to connect to. In this case, the port number is 25900.

After that, the `-i` option specifies the private key file (in this case, "~/UserKey.pem") that the user will use to authenticate themselves.

The `-C` option tells SSH to prompt the user for a password before connecting.

Finally, the `user@ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com` is the IP address of the remote server that the user wants to connect to.
